# AeroLIT PXE Content

AeroLIT PXE Content is a container image that serves dynamic PXE boot content for AeroLIT provisioning workflows.

It generates and serves:

- `boot.ipxe`
- Kickstart files under `/ks`
- a simple web index
- generated status and validation reports
- profile-driven install menus for detected RHEL ISO trees

The image is intended to be a lightweight PXE content layer. It does not replace Foreman, DHCP, TFTP, Ansible, or the AeroLIT bootstrap workflow. It provides the HTTP-served PXE menu and Kickstart content those workflows can use.

## What this image does

At startup, the image runs Nginx and the PXE content generator.

The generator detects supported ISO trees, reads built-in and override profile definitions, renders Kickstart files, creates `boot.ipxe`, and writes status files.

Supported ISO tree names are:

```text
rhel7iso
rhel8iso
rhel9iso
rhel10iso
```

A valid ISO tree must include:

```text
images/pxeboot/vmlinuz
images/pxeboot/initrd.img
```

For RHEL 8, 9, and 10, repository metadata should also exist under:

```text
BaseOS/repodata/repomd.xml
AppStream/repodata/repomd.xml
```

For RHEL 7, repository metadata should exist under:

```text
repodata/repomd.xml
```

Missing repository metadata creates a warning because PXE boot files may exist even though the install content is incomplete.

