## Built-in profiles

Current profile sets are defined under:

```text
content/profiles/
```

Implemented profiles generate real boot targets and Kickstarts.

Placeholder profiles appear in the menu, but they do not generate real install targets or real Kickstart references.

Current profile intent:

```text
developer_workstation   placeholder
security_baseline       placeholder
security_luks           placeholder
embedded_edge           placeholder
minimal                 implemented
small_disk              implemented
```

## Quick start

Example container run:

```bash
podman run --rm -d \
  --name pxe-content \
  -p 18080:8080 \
  -e PXE_SERVER=<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname> \
  -e PXE_PORT=18080 \
  -v /path/to/extracted_isos:/iso:Z \
  -v /path/to/overrides:/overrides:Z \
  registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/pxe-content:latest
```

Then open or test:

```text
http://<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname>:18080/
http://<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname>:18080/boot.ipxe
http://<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname>:18080/generated/status.txt
http://<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname>:18080/generated/status.json
```

For iPXE testing, the chain command normally looks like:

```ipxe
chain http://<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname>:18080/boot.ipxe
```

## Common environment variables

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|---|---:|---|
| `PXE_SERVER` | required | Server name or IP used in generated PXE URLs |
| `PXE_PORT` | `18080` | External HTTP port used in generated PXE URLs |
| `PXE_ISO_ROOT` | `/iso` | Container path where extracted ISO trees are mounted |
| `PXE_HTML_ROOT` | `/etc/nginx/html` | Web root where generated content is written |
| `PXE_TEMPLATE_ROOT` | `/templates` | Built-in Kickstart template root |
| `PXE_PROFILE_ROOT` | `/profiles` | Built-in profile definition root |
| `PXE_OVERRIDE_ROOT` | `/overrides` | Main customization root |
| `PXE_GENERATED_KS_EDIT_POLICY` | `preserve` | Controls manual edits under generated `/ks` |
| `PXE_VALIDATION_FAILURE_POLICY` | `warn` | Controls whether validation errors fail generation |
| `PXE_WATCH_INTERVAL` | `15` | Seconds between generator watch checks |
| `ROOTPW_HASH` | built-in default | Root password hash used in generated Kickstarts |
| `ALLOW_DEFAULT_ROOTPW` | `true` | Allows the built-in default password hash |

The default root password is only for lab/bootstrap use. Set `ROOTPW_HASH` for real use.

## Generated files

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/boot.ipxe` | Main iPXE menu |
| `/ks/*.ks` | Generated Kickstart files |
| `/index.html` | Basic browser landing page |
| `/generated/status.json` | Machine-readable generator status and validation report |
| `/generated/status.txt` | Human-readable status report |
| `/generated/isos.txt` | Detected ISO inventory |
| `/generated/kickstart-state/` | State used to detect manual edits |
| `/generated/preserved-kickstarts/` | Candidate files created when manual edits are preserved |

## Testing the image

The image includes a built-in test runner.

Run all tests against the image:

```bash
podman run --rm \
  --entrypoint /usr/local/bin/pxe-content-test \
  registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/pxe-content:test \
  all
```

This validates the generator, profiles, templates, override behavior, preserve/overwrite policy, validation failure policy, generated status files, and basic HTTP serving without requiring real PXE hardware.

See:

```text
docs/testing.md
```

## Customization overview

Preferred customization path:

```text
/overrides/profiles/
/overrides/templates/
```

Example override files are stored in:

```text
content/examples/overrides/
```

Use overrides when you want repeatable changes.

Manual edits under generated `/ks` are supported as an emergency path. By default, manual edits are preserved and regenerated content is written as a candidate file under:

```text
/generated/preserved-kickstarts/
```

Use `PXE_GENERATED_KS_EDIT_POLICY=overwrite` to allow the generator to replace manual `/ks` edits.

